<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1230" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1230">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6266A/6–1244</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Apostolic Delegate in the United States</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cicognani</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-03">July 3,
                                1944</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Archbishop</hi>: With further reference to
                            your letter of June 12, 1944 (file no. 171/44) concerning the temporary
                            detention by the Allied military authorities of two members of the
                            German Embassy to the Holy See, I am happy to inform you that
                            instructions have gone forward to the Supreme Allied Commander to
                            release these individuals and permit them to enter Vatican City.</p>
                        <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cordell Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>